    <div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><h2>Ingredients</h2>

<ul>
<li>250g boiled (and cooled) chick peas</li>
<li>75g olive oil</li>
<li>50g lemon juice</li>
<li>50g brine (this can be obtained from a tin of "cooked chickpeas in brine"! Alternatively, just mix some salt and water)</li>
<li>50g Tahini (pulped roasted seseme seeds)</li>
<li>1 small clove of garlic</li>
</ul>

<h2>Method<br/>
 <br/>
Blend all ingredients in an electric blender. Done.</h2>

<h2>Variations</h2>

<p>Try adding a roasted red pepper, a little corriander and a little cumin. If you're feeling dangerous, add a little chilli too.</p></div>
